@mxruka:  

No, they won't be able to search their library for the basic land unless they pay the {2} as they try to do so. This stops ALL searching through libraries for everyone, unless the fee is paid.  

This is bringing me ever closer to building a white artifact deck. We'll see what happens when my Scars booster box arrives. <3

@Perrlin: Look at the ability of [Foresee](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Foresee) "To scry X, look at the top X cards of your library, then put any number of them on the bottom of your library and the rest on top in any order." You are not *searching* for cards, you are merely *looking* at the top X cards of your library, ergo, you do not have to pay 2 for the [Leonin Arbiter](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Leonin Arbiter)'s ability.  

The card itself, though, mana/titan ramp decks, BEWARE!! Garfield has sit his fat arse in your way to getting those nasty combos. Although, if you are playing R/G (as stated by previous comments) ramp you would save your burn spells for it. \*COUGH\*[Arc Trail](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Arc Trail)\*COUGH\*  
